{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set st = card_data.statistics %}
{% set ab = card_data.alt_beta %}
{% set dd = card_data.drawdown_band %}
{% set sharpe_scale_lo = [st.sharpe_reported.ci_lo, st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_lo] | min %}
{% set sharpe_scale_hi = [st.sharpe_reported.ci_hi, st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_hi] | max %}
{% set sharpe_zero_pct = (0 - sharpe_scale_lo) / (sharpe_scale_hi - sharpe_scale_lo) * 100 %}
{% set drawdown_floor = dd.p99 | min %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/s2.css?v={{ asset_version }}">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_lead %}
<div class="tearsheet-lead">
<section class="tearsheet-decision" id="s2-decision-takeaway" aria-labelledby="s2-decision-title">
  <p class="tearsheet-eyebrow">Decision takeaway</p>
  <h2 id="s2-decision-title">Keep monitoring. Do not add on the point estimates.</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Decision:</strong> keep collecting evidence and open a fees-for-beta
    conversation. The 48-month intervals do not separate skill from noise and factor
    exposure, so the positive points do not support a conviction add.
  </p>
  <p class="tearsheet-decision__sample">
    Synthetic manager <strong>{{ card_data.meta.manager_name }}</strong> · equity
    long/short · {{ card_data.meta.months }} months · tier {{ card_data.meta.tier }} ·
    risk-free {{ "%.1f"|format(card_data.meta.rf_annual * 100) }}%/yr
    <span class="tearsheet-synthetic">(synthetic)</span>
  </p>
</section>

<figure class="tearsheet-focal" id="s2-focal-comparison"
        aria-labelledby="s2-focal-title" aria-describedby="s2-focal-caption">
  <div class="tearsheet-focal__intro">
    <p class="tearsheet-eyebrow">Focal comparison</p>
    <h2 id="s2-focal-title">Smoothing made the track record look more precise than it is.</h2>
    <p>
      Undoing smoothed marks lowers the Sharpe from
      {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_reported.point) }} to
      {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_desmoothed.point) }}. Both 95% intervals cross zero,
      so the economic correction changes the estimate without resolving the skill call.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="tearsheet-stat-pair">
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="sharpe"
         data-lo="{{ st.sharpe_reported.ci_lo }}"
         data-point="{{ st.sharpe_reported.point }}"
         data-hi="{{ st.sharpe_reported.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">Reported Sharpe</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_reported.point) }}</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail">
        <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
        <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="interval-stat__scale" aria-label="Shared Sharpe scale from {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_scale_lo) }} to {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_scale_hi) }}">
        <span>{{ "%.2f"|format(sharpe_scale_lo) }}</span>
        <span class="interval-stat__zero-label" style="left: {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_zero_pct) }}%">0</span>
        <span>{{ "%.2f"|format(sharpe_scale_hi) }}</span>
      </div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">95% interval {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_reported.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_reported.ci_hi) }}</span>
    </div>

    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="sharpe"
         data-lo="{{ st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_lo }}"
         data-point="{{ st.sharpe_desmoothed.point }}"
         data-hi="{{ st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">De-smoothed Sharpe</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_desmoothed.point) }}</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail">
        <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
        <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="interval-stat__scale" aria-label="Shared Sharpe scale from {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_scale_lo) }} to {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_scale_hi) }}">
        <span>{{ "%.2f"|format(sharpe_scale_lo) }}</span>
        <span class="interval-stat__zero-label" style="left: {{ '%.2f'|format(sharpe_zero_pct) }}%">0</span>
        <span>{{ "%.2f"|format(sharpe_scale_hi) }}</span>
      </div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">95% interval {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%.2f"|format(st.sharpe_desmoothed.ci_hi) }}</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="tearsheet-mppm">
    Smoothing kernel &theta; = ({{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.theta[0]) }},
    {{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.theta[1]) }}, {{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.theta[2]) }});
    economic/reported volatility ratio {{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.unsmoothing.vol_ratio) }}.
    MPPM (&rho;=3) is {{ "%+.1f"|format(st.mppm.point * 100) }}%/yr; read the
    Sharpe&ndash;MPPM gap as a manipulation check, not another ranking score.
  </p>
  <figcaption id="s2-focal-caption" class="tearsheet-interpretation">
    <strong>What it changes.</strong> The de-smoothed estimate is the defensible basis
    for underwriting. <strong>What remains uncertain.</strong> The interval is still too
    wide to support either a skill or no-skill conclusion.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="tearsheet-panel tearsheet-further-analysis" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <p class="tearsheet-eyebrow">Further analysis</p>
  <h2 class="tearsheet-panel__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <p class="tearsheet-note">
    The focal comparison corrects the headline risk-adjusted return. The panels below
    ask the next two questions: whether the residual return clears factor uncertainty,
    and whether the realized loss is unusual under the maintained skill hypothesis.
  </p>
  <p class="tearsheet-note">
    This known-truth construction exercises de-smoothing, interval estimation, factor
    attribution, and drawdown-refusal mechanics. It does not establish external
    calibration, predictive accuracy, or a conclusion about a live manager.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="tearsheet-panel">
  <h2 class="tearsheet-panel__title">Factor regression &mdash; interval alpha</h2>
  <p class="tearsheet-note">
    The factor model tests whether the remaining return can be distinguished from zero
    after the estimated exposures are removed.
  </p>
  <div class="tearsheet-factor">
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="alpha"
         data-lo="{{ st.alpha.ci_lo }}"
         data-point="{{ st.alpha.point }}"
         data-hi="{{ st.alpha.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">Annualized alpha</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%+.1f"|format(st.alpha.point * 100) }}%</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail">
        <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
        <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">90% interval {{ "%+.1f"|format(st.alpha.ci_lo * 100) }}% &hellip; {{ "%+.1f"|format(st.alpha.ci_hi * 100) }}%</span>
    </div>
    <dl class="tearsheet-betas">
      <dt>Market</dt><dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.factor_betas.market) }}</dd>
      <dt>Size</dt><dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.factor_betas.size) }}</dd>
      <dt>Value</dt><dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.factor_betas.value) }}</dd>
      <dt>Momentum</dt><dd>{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.factor_betas.momentum) }}</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>
  <div class="tearsheet-altbeta">
    <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="shrink">{{ ab.chip }}</span>
    <span class="tearsheet-altbeta__ci">
      alpha {{ "%.0f"|format(ab.level * 100) }}% CI
      {{ "%+.1f"|format(ab.ci_lo * 100) }}% &hellip; {{ "%+.1f"|format(ab.ci_hi * 100) }}%
      &mdash; not distinguishable from factor beta at this track length.
    </span>
  </div>
  <p class="tearsheet-interpretation">
    <strong>What it changes.</strong> A positive alpha point is not treated as
    demonstrated alpha. <strong>What remains uncertain.</strong> The record permits both
    useful skill and no residual alpha after factor exposure.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="tearsheet-panel">
  <h2 class="tearsheet-panel__title" id="s2-drawdown-title">Drawdown vs simulation-calibrated null</h2>
  <figure class="tearsheet-chart" aria-labelledby="s2-drawdown-title s2-drawdown-caption">
    <div class="tearsheet-chart__plot">
      <div class="tearsheet-chart__y-axis" aria-hidden="true">
        <span>0%</span>
        <strong>Drawdown (%)</strong>
        <span>{{ "%.0f"|format(drawdown_floor * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <svg class="s2-drawdown" viewBox="0 0 100 40" preserveAspectRatio="none"
           role="img" aria-label="Realized drawdown against the pointwise null envelope"></svg>
    </div>
    <div class="tearsheet-chart__x-axis" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>Month 1</span><span>Month {{ card_data.meta.months }}</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="tearsheet-chart__legend" aria-label="Drawdown chart legend">
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--realized"></span>Realized drawdown</li>
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--median"></span>Median path</li>
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--p95"></span>95th-percentile envelope</li>
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--p99"></span>99th-percentile envelope</li>
    </ul>
    <figcaption id="s2-drawdown-caption" class="tearsheet-interpretation">
      <strong>What it changes.</strong> The realized path
      <strong>stays within the 99th-percentile envelope</strong>, so this exhibit
      supplies no loss alarm.
      <strong>What remains uncertain.</strong> The bands are pointwise, not a
      familywise-calibrated rule for repeated monitoring.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
</section>

<section class="tearsheet-panel">
  <h2 class="tearsheet-panel__title" id="s2-returns-title">Monthly returns</h2>
  <figure class="tearsheet-chart" aria-labelledby="s2-returns-title s2-returns-caption">
    <div class="tearsheet-chart__plot tearsheet-chart__plot--returns">
      <div class="tearsheet-chart__y-axis" aria-hidden="true">
        <span>+</span>
        <strong>Monthly net return (%)</strong>
        <span>&minus;</span>
      </div>
      <svg class="s2-strip" viewBox="0 0 100 30" preserveAspectRatio="none"
           role="img" aria-label="Monthly net return strip in percent"></svg>
    </div>
    <div class="tearsheet-chart__x-axis" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>Month 1</span><span>Month {{ card_data.meta.months }}</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="tearsheet-chart__legend" aria-label="Monthly return chart legend">
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--positive"></span>Positive month</li>
      <li><span class="tearsheet-key tearsheet-key--negative"></span>Negative month</li>
    </ul>
    <figcaption id="s2-returns-caption" class="tearsheet-interpretation">
      <strong>What it changes.</strong> The strip makes clustering and sign changes
      visible instead of hiding the path inside one annualized statistic.
      <strong>What remains uncertain.</strong> A return strip does not explain the
      economic cause of a month or establish persistence.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>Six pure stages over the return series and a fully synthetic factor set:
unsmoothing (Getmansky&ndash;Lo&ndash;Makarov MA(2)), factor regression, interval
machinery (Lo SE + Ledoit&ndash;Wolf bootstrap for the Sharpe, Newey&ndash;West for the
alpha), MPPM, and the simulation-calibrated drawdown band. Every statistic is an
interval; a bare point is a design-system error.</p>
<p>The alt-beta chip is a <em>calibration statement about track length</em>, not an
accusation: the alpha's 90% interval includes zero at 48 months, which opens a
fees-for-beta conversation &mdash; it does not claim the manager has no skill.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/s2-tearsheet.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
